metadata.name: Phantoms #240
metadata.description:
Phantoms is a series of hazy memories of distant places. Some tranquil, others sinister, each scene is as much defined by what is revealed as by what remains unseen.

In this collection I aim to juxtapose hard and soft. Blocky shapes form the core of the compositions. Upon these surfaces, soft textures appear to flow and drip over the sides. Varying levels of opacity, lighting, and fog effects further soften the scenes to create an atmospheric, dream-like quality. By remaining semi-abstract, each of the color palettes are given the space to influence the mood dramatically.

metadata.name: PAPERCUTS #13
metadata.description:
PAPERCUTS is a playful series that brings elements of paper cuts to the project concept. It all started with some colored papers, scissors and glue, the handmade work became a reference for digital creations.

5 different styles [simple, random-up-down, up-down, highlighted-columns-up-down, lines]

4 color pallets

2 grid sizes: 6x6 and 8x8

metadata.name: Laser Paintings #1
metadata.description:
Scorch and tear this darkness inbued canvas with raycasted lasers.

This one is a pretty obscure project of mine, I just love the way those rays pierce through the darkness with some pixel-bound imperfections that can sometimes generate refraction.
(best consumed in a dark environment or surrounding frame)

12 kinds of solid darkness patterns:
 - Pebbles
 - Sparse
 - Bars
 - Structure
 - Clouds
 - Dotgrid
 - Globuli
 - FX
 - Dashes
 - Flowers
 - Concentrism
 - Sines

6 kinds of light sources (with variations):
 - Points
 - Line
 - Drips
 - Laser
 - Scan

during each frame 128 rays are casted and bounce 64 times

made with vanilla js (no shaders, just 2 canvases and trigonometry)

Click to show the generation progress in you browser's console
Click when the rendering has ended to add an other pass!

metadata.name: Generational Differences #107
metadata.description:
Based on 1-dimensional cellular automata, different pleasing patterns are produced by each generation changing the rules for the next one. Each token will produce a unique sequence of patterns, like a slideshow of mosaics. Transitions may be subtle or very drastical, since a small change on the rules has a huge effect.
Best enjoyed on fullscreen

Click anywhere on the canvas to stop/resume the creation of new generations.
Press s to download at the current resolution

Original minters will get 50% of the royalties

metadata.name: A Slight Case of Overbombing #177
metadata.description:
Inspired by monochromatic art of the late 60s, Russian folk-art woodblock prints, and the stylised colours of British underground comics, excited to introduce a series of bold rich landscapes. England, Wales, Ireland and Scotland represented by red, yellow, green and blue, sometimes a house or two, and groovy clouds.

Instructions ::

.     - speed up
,     - slow down
space - pause
n     - toggle noise
p     - cycle palette
h     - toggle high-res (and definitely intentional pixel shift)
s     - download and save image

metadata.name: Reconnaissance #392
metadata.description:
An immense quiet accompanies a sense of looming futility while peering down across vast new worlds. What use is there in discovering and documenting these unknown places? Who would care to seek out lifeless lands lost in the cosmos?

Any civilization capable of such reconnaissance might seem above the little hope that barren lands may bring. Unless, of course, there is a hope of answering the most desperate of needs: Finding a New Home.

Were these images captured by humans on Earth, or on Mars, or somewhere even further away in distance and probability? Maybe they’re recon from another planet’s civilization — one that shares our struggle to find true harmony with the world they have.

Inspired by the remarkable satellite imagery in the compendium “This is Mars,” Reconnaissance suggests what may lie outside our habitable lands — and that we risk missing what's already here while being compelled to look further and further for what’s next.


Choose a resolution (1-6) by adding "&scale=4" to the URL in live view.
Created with p5.js

TENDER x Nat Sarkissian
May 2022

metadata.name: Botany #146
metadata.description:
This project started as an exploration of shapes focused on the peaceful feeling that stands out in a floral composition. Amplified by the sketch and toon rendering engine allow the piece to create an infinite amount of satisfying graphic composition.

The piece is draggable and interactive, giving it a sense of tangibility that I find very satisfying. 

It comes in various schemes and styles, each feature is further described in the features section. 

If you are interested in a printed version of your mint, don't hesitate to reach out to me on Twitter so I can render a High resolution and send you a print. 
(Price may vary depending on the demands)

Made in native Webgl and Javascript, by @LodsDorian

metadata.name: Madone Solitaire #114
metadata.description:
“Madone Solitaire” is a series of generative drawings inspired by Japanese art and "Les fleurs du mal" by French author Charles Baudelaire.

Features:

- 30 color palettes 

- 3 background layers

- 3 different formats (square, portrait, and landscape)

-  50% chance of mountains 

Made with p5.js

Patricio Isaías, April 2022
